<headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued June 23 at 3:48PM MDT until June 23 at 4:45PM MDT by NWS Glasgow</headline>
<description>The National Weather Service in Glasgow has issued a
* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Southwestern Daniels County in northeastern Montana...
Northwestern Roosevelt County in northeastern Montana...
East central Valley County in northeastern Montana...
* Until 445 PM MDT.
* At 347 PM MDT, a severe thunderstorm was located near St. Marie, or
19 miles northeast of Glasgow, moving east at 40 mph.
HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and small hail.
SOURCE...Radar Indicated.
IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.
* Locations impacted include...
Lustre and Volt.
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
